						               													<description>Wo war's? Mini revisits the Roberto Fraga title of 2009 in which players tried to track down invisible creatures, but instead of listening to an electronic device give clues, one of the players in the game now takes the role of the red dragon and gives clues to a thief's location to everyone else.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;At the start of the game, the dragon player takes a &amp;quot;clue track&amp;quot; and slides it into a device that only she can see. She then makes animal noises for all of the animals on the game board so that the other players know what sounds she'll make during the game. The dragon player makes a sound corresponding to the first space on the clue track, of which there will be several locations on the game board, then the other players roll a die and start moving toward where they think the thief might be. The dragon player makes another clue, then the players move, and so on. If the players are on the thief's location at the end of the round, they each earn a dragon token; otherwise, the dragon player earns a token.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Have each player be the dragon once, and whoever collects the most tokens by the end of the game wins.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
